{"Id":"b1358bc5-5a6d-4ff7-aed8-b47c1ccbcdd3","Title":"Adafruit DC+Stepper Motor HAT","Description":"<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd\">\n<html><head><meta name=\"qrichtext\" content=\"1\" /><style type=\"text/css\">\np, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }\n</style></head><body style=\" font-family:'MS Shell Dlg 2'; font-size:8.25pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;\">\n<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Let your robotic dreams come true with the new DC+Stepper Motor HAT from Adafruit. This Raspberry Pi add-on is perfect for any motion project as it can drive up to 4 DC or 2 Stepper motors with full PWM speed control. </p>\n<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Since the Raspberry Pi does not have a lot of PWM pins, we use a<span style=\" font-family:'Gotham SSm A,Gotham SSm B,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif'; font-size:14px; color:#000000;\"> </span><span style=\" font-weight:600;\">fully-dedicated PWM driver chip</span><span style=\" font-family:'Gotham SSm A,Gotham SSm B,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif'; font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#000000;\"> </span>onboard to both control motor direction and speed. This chip handles all the motor and speed controls over I2C. Only two pins (SDA &amp; SCL) are required to drive the multiple motors, and since it's I2C you can also connect any other I2C devices or HATs to the same pins. </p>\n<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">In fact, <span style=\" font-weight:600;\">you can even stack multiple Motor HATs</span>, up to 32 of them, for controlling up to 64 stepper motors or 128 DC motors (or a mix of the two) - just remember to purchase and solder in a stacking header instead of the one we include. </p>\n<p style=\" margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\">Motors are controlled by TB6612 MOSFET drivers with 1.2A per channel current capability (you can draw up to 3A peak for approx 20ms at a time)<span style=\" font-family:'Gotham SSm A,Gotham SSm B,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif'; font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#000000;\">, </span>a big improvement over L293D drivers and there are built-in flyback diodes as well.</p></body></html>","Author":"ladyada","Source":"Fritzing library 'Adafruit Raspberry Pi.fzbz'","Properties":{"part number":"Adafruit #2348","fritzingModelIndex":"85430333","family":"Adafruit DC+Stepper Motor HAT","variant":"variant 1","layer":null,"fritzingVersion":"0.5.2b.02.18.4756","fritzingPartVersion":"4","fritzingDate":"Sat Aug 20 2016","fritzingModuleId":"adafruit_b3cce8e3310d632bbfe3bbb334ab8858_1"},"Tags":[],"Views":{"breadboard":{"ViewType":"breadboard","ViewImageRef":"breadboard\\adafruit_b3cce8e3310d632bbfe3bbb334ab8858_5_breadboard.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":2.55906,"NativeHeightInInches":2.22441,"Layers":{}},"schematic":{"ViewType":"schematic","ViewImageRef":"schematic\\adafruit_b3cce8e3310d632bbfe3bbb334ab8858_5_schematic.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":1.6,"NativeHeightInInches":2.9,"Layers":{}},"pcb":{"ViewType":"pcb","ViewImageRef":"pcb\\adafruit_b3cce8e3310d632bbfe3bbb334ab8858_5_pcb.xaml","NativeWidthInInches":2.55906,"NativeHeightInInches":2.22441,"Layers":{}}}}